// The `/=` ASCII synonym for `‚Č†` must normalize to `‚Č†` under BOTH parsers
// when written as `operator /=` (regression for the RD/LALR divergence where
// the recursive-descent parser left the identifier as the literal `/=`).
// `‚Č†` is built-in equality sugar, not a definable value, so referring to it as
// `operator /=` is an undefined variable under either parser -- but the error
// must name `‚Č†`, proving the ASCII synonym was normalized.
define d = operator /=
